# Project Overview

This project is a portfolio-safe Power BI dashboard replica developed using mock data inspired by a real freelance analytics engagement in the poultry and agri-input industry.

The dashboards were designed to analyze:

Revenue performance
Product demand
Pricing sensitivity
Customer lifecycle
User engagement
Sales channel effectiveness

All data has been anonymized and recreated to ensure client confidentiality and data privacy.

# Business Objective

The objective of this analysis was to help the business:

Identify top-performing products and districts
Understand customer purchase behavior
Optimize discount and pricing strategy
Improve customer retention
Increase revenue through channel and product analysis
Support data-driven business decisions

# Key Insights, Recommendations & Business Impact
# 1. Revenue Is Concentrated in Specific Districts

# Key Insight
- Hooghly (5.9M) and Mysuru (4.5M) generated the highest revenue among all districts.

# Recommendation
- Increase sales investment and inventory availability in top-performing districts.
- Replicate successful sales strategies in lower-performing regions.

# Business Impact
- Maximizes ROI from high-performing markets.
- Improves regional expansion strategy and resource allocation.

# 2. Bio-Security Foot Bath & Automatic Bell Drinker Drive Maximum Revenue

# Key Insight
- These products consistently generated the highest net revenue contribution across channels.
- Prioritize these SKUs in promotions and inventory planning.
- Bundle them with slower-moving products to improve cross-selling.

# Business Impact
- Increases profitability through high-demand product optimization.
- Reduces inventory stagnation for low-performing products.

# 3. App Channel Outperformed Web & Field Channels

# Key Insight
- The App channel generated significantly higher revenue (~1.22M) compared to Web (~0.70M) and Field sales.

# Recommendation
- Focus on mobile-first campaigns and app-exclusive offers.
- Improve mobile user experience and digital onboarding.

#Business Impact
- Boosts digital adoption and reduces offline operational dependency.
- Improves customer convenience and repeat purchases.

# 4. Customers Aged 31–40 Generated Highest Order Volume
Key Insight
- The 31–35 and 36–40 age groups contributed the largest share of orders.

# Recommendation
- Target this demographic with personalized marketing campaigns and loyalty offers.
- Build customer personas around this core buyer segment.

# Business Impact
- Improves conversion rates and campaign effectiveness.
- Enhances customer acquisition efficiency.

# 5. Purchase Gap Averaged 96 Days
# Key Insight
- Customers typically reordered products after approximately three months.

# Recommendation
- Launch automated reminder campaigns before the 90-day repurchase cycle.
- Introduce subscription or replenishment models.

# Business Impact
- Improves customer retention and repeat sales.
- Reduces churn risk through proactive engagement.

# 6. Feed Category Received Highest Discounting (64.8%)

# Key Insight
- Feed products had significantly higher discounts compared to other categories.

# Recommendation
- Evaluate whether discounts are increasing profitability or only driving volume.
- Optimize discounting using margin-based pricing strategies.

# Business Impact
- Protects profit margins while maintaining sales growth.
- Improves pricing efficiency.

# 7. Bulk Buyers Purchased More Frequently Than Small Buyers

# Key Insight
- Bulk buyers showed higher purchase frequency (668 vs 532).

# Recommendation
- Create loyalty programs and credit benefits for bulk buyers.
- Develop distributor-focused engagement strategies.

# Business Impact
- Strengthens long-term customer relationships.
- Increases customer lifetime value.

# 8. Poultry Feed & Bio-Supplements Dominated Product Demand

# Key Insight
- These categories showed the highest quantity movement and platform engagement.

# Recommendation
- Maintain higher stock levels for high-demand categories.
- Forecast demand using seasonal trend analysis.

# Business Impact
- Prevents stockouts and revenue loss.
- Improves supply chain planning.

# 9. Hibernating & At-Risk Customers Were Significant Segments

# Key Insight
- A considerable number of customers showed declining activity in RFM analysis.

# Recommendation
- Launch reactivation campaigns with personalized offers.
- Use engagement triggers through WhatsApp and email automation.

# Business Impact
- Reduces customer churn.
- Improves retention without high acquisition costs.

# 10. Revenue Spikes Were Campaign-Driven

# Key Insight
- Revenue trend analysis showed irregular spikes reaching up to 531K and 451K on certain dates.

# Recommendation
- Analyze successful campaigns and replicate their timing and structure.
- Align inventory and staffing during high-demand periods.

# Business Impact
- Improves campaign planning and forecasting accuracy.
- Helps scale successful sales strategies.

